The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Umrigar in hospital

Mumbai: Former India skipper Polly Umrigar is undergoing a series of tests at the Bombay Hospital, after being admitted to the ICU three days ago, according to a source close to the 80-year-old cricketer. 

Various tests are being done to find out the degree of ailment and to ascertain the line of treatment that would be required, he said. (PTI) 




